To run the st-tests.py unit tests, you will need the following environment
variables set (shown here with an example path):

setenv ESPA_UNIT_TEST_DATA_DIR /LOSRLPGD02/data2/rockvam/level2_test_data
setenv ST_DATA_DIR /pcache/level1/dev/rockvam/level2/software/espa-surface-temperature/st/static_data
setenv MERRA2_AUX_DIR /pcache/level1/dev/rockvam/level2/auxiliary/LST/sample_orig_NARR_MERRA
setenv NARR_AUX_DIR /usr/local/usgs/bridge/auxiliaries/LST/NARR
setenv ASTER_GED_SERVER lsdslb:7480
setenv ASTER_GED_PATH /AG100.003/
setenv MODTRAN_DATA_DIR /pcache/level1/dev/rockvam/level2/auxiliary/MODTRAN_DATA
setenv NUM_THREADS 4 (optional)

To run a single test: python -m unittest st-tests.TestGridPoints
